<!DOCTYPE html><html ⚡ lang="de"><head> <% include ../_partials/amp/_amp-head.ejs %><script async custom-element="amp-sidebar" src="https://cdn.ampproject.org/v0/amp-sidebar-0.1.js"></script><script async custom-element="amp-accordion" src="https://cdn.ampproject.org/v0/amp-accordion-0.1.js"></script><script async custom-element="amp-form" src="https://cdn.ampproject.org/v0/amp-form-0.1.js"></script><script async custom-element="amp-image-lightbox" src="https://cdn.ampproject.org/v0/amp-image-lightbox-0.1.js"></script></head><body class="home"><amp-sidebar id='sidebar' side='right' layout='nodisplay'> <% include ../_partials/amp/_ampLandingSidebar.ejs %></amp-sidebar><header class="header fixed"> <% include ../_partials/amp/_amp-header.ejs %></header><div class="wrap mobile-down"><div class="content"><section class="hero internetAccess"><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="six columns"><div class="intro-container"><h1>Alarm Funktion</h1><p class="intro"> <strong>Alarm Aufnahme</strong><br><br> Um unter Windows Vista / 7 / 8 aufzuzeichnen müssen Sie die IP Adresse Ihrer Kamera zu den vertrauenswürdigen Seiten hinzufügen. Dafür gehen Sie bitte im Internet Explorer unter Tools - Internetoptionen - Sicherheit - Vertrauenswürdige Seiten - Seiten um die IP Adresse Ihrer Kamera hinzuzufügen. Sie müssen den Haken unter Benötigte Server Verifizierung (https:) für alle Seiten in dieser Zone entfernen, sodass Sie die IP als http eintragen können. Danach geben Sie bitte die IP-Adresse in der Adressleiste Ihres Webbrowsers ein und Sie sollten dementsprechend den<a href="/Web_User_Interface/HD_Series/Video_Menu_Bar/">Pfad aufzeichnen</a> können. Falls Sie den Pfad immer noch nicht aufzeichnen können, stellen Sie bitte sicher, dass Sie den Internet Explorer mit Administratorrechten gestartet haben.</p></div></div></div></div></section></div></div><div class="wrap"><div class="container main"> <% include ../_partials/content/_bluenav-general.ejs %><article class="blade wrapper content"><div><h1>Manual Recording with FullHD-, HD-, or VGA-Cameras</h1><h2>FullHD-Camera</h2></div><div class="margin"><h3>Snapshot/Manual Video Recording</h3><p>If you want to take a snapshot of the live-video just press the camera-button on the right side. If you click on the camcorder-symbol next to it, you can start a video record. By clicking the symbol again, the video record will be stopped.</p></div><div class="margin"><amp-img on="tap:Recording_Manual_1080p_01" role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/Motion_Detection/Recording_Manual_1080p_01.png" width="1351" height="672" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img></div><div class="margin"><p>All records will be saved to the SD-Card of the Camera and can be accesed by clicking on <strong>SD-Card</strong> in the upper bar. As an alternative, for example to easily save specific records, you can use an application on your computer. For a variety of applications click <a href="/Motion_Detection/SD_Card_Access/">here</a>.<br> You can also use our free App for <a href="/Software/Android/InstarVision/Recording/">Android</a>, <a href="/Software/iOS/InstarVision/iPhone/Recording/">iPhone</a>, <a href="/Software/iOS/InstarVision/iPad/Recording/">iPad</a> and <a href="/Software/Windows/InstarVision/Windows_Phone/Recording/">Windows Phone</a> to remotely access the <a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Features/SD_Card/">SD-Card</a>.</p></div><div class="margin"><p>Please be reminded that during the manual recording, the video will be divided into smaller videos. In the menu under <a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Features/Manual_Recording/">Features - Manual Record</a> you can find the controls to set the length of the video-parts. We recommend a video-part-length of 10-15 minutes to avoid the risk of data-loss.</p></div><div class="margin"><h3>Scheduled Audio- & Video Record</h3><p> Your camera can record Audio- & Video following a schedule. To set up the schedule navigate to <a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Recording/Video/">Tasks</a>. Here you can choose between photo series and video record and then can set up their individual schedule:</p></div><div class="margin clearfix"><amp-img on="tap:Recording_Schedule_1080p_ENG_01" role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/Motion_Detection/Recording_Schedule_1080p_ENG_01.png" width="739" height="537" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img></div><div><h2>HD-Camera</h2><h3>Snapshot/Manual Video Recording</h3><p>If you want to take a snapshot of the live-video just click on <strong>Snapshot to SD</strong> in the upper bar. If you click on <strong>Recording: SD</strong> next to it, you can start a video record. By clicking the symbol again, the video record will be stopped.</p></div><div class="margin"><amp-img on="tap:Recording_Manual_720p_01" role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/Motion_Detection/Recording_Manual_720p_01.png" width="700" height="393" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img></div><div class="margin"><p>All records will be saved to the SD-Card of the Camera and can be accesed by clicking on <strong>SD-Card</strong> in the upper bar. As an alternative, for example to easily save specific records, you can use an application on your computer. For a variety of applications click <a href="/Motion_Detection/SD_Card_Access/">here</a>.<br> You can also use our free App for <a href="/Software/Android/InstarVision/Recording/">Android</a>, <a href="/Software/iOS/InstarVision/iPhone/Recording/">iPhone</a>, <a href="/Software/iOS/InstarVision/iPad/Recording/">iPad</a> and <a href="/Software/Windows/InstarVision/Windows_Phone/Recording/">Windows Phone</a> to remotely access the <a href="/Web_User_Interface/1080p_Series/Features/SD_Card/">SD-Card</a>.</p><div class="margin"><p>Please be reminded that during the manual recording, the video will be divided into smaller videos. In the menu under <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Recording/Video/">Features - Manual Record</a> you can find the controls to set the length of the video-parts. We recommend a video-part-length of 10-15 minutes to avoid the risk of data-loss.</p></div><div class="margin"><h3>Scheduled Audio- & Video Record</h3><p> Your camera can record Audio- & Video following a schedule. To set up the schedule navigate to <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Recording/Video/">Recoding</a>. Here you can choose between photo series and video record and then can set up their individual schedule:</p></div><div class="margin"><amp-img on="tap:Recording_Manual_720p_02" role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/Motion_Detection/Recording_Manual_720p_02.png" width="700" height="393" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img></div><div class="margin"><h2>VGA-Camera</h2><p> The VGA-Camera is using the ActiveX-Plugin to record videos. This plugin is only being supported on Windows Internet Explorer. Under <strong>Alarm - Path</strong> you can chooose the path for the reordings, by clicking on <strong>Record</strong> in the upper bar, you can start the recording.<br/><br/> In order to record in Windows 8 / 7 / Vista you will need to add the IP address of your IP camera to the list of trusted sites. In order to do so please open your Internet Explorer and go to Tools - Internet Options - Security - Trusted sites - Sites to add the IP address of your camera. You will need to remove the checkmark by Require server verification (https:) for all sites in this zone so that you can add the IP as http. After that please reload the cameras ip address in your web browser and you should be able to set the record path accordingly. If you can still not set the record path please make sure you have started the Internet Explorer with admin rights.</div><div class="margin"><p>The recording with (1 frame per second) is possible if you are recording with FTP upload. The camera can upload a picture every second in case of an alarm. All you need is a FTP server or a network HDD which can also be set with an FTP access. You can also record the video with our additional software INSTARVISION or any other THIRD PARTY SOFTWARE. If you are using a QNAP or SYNOLOGY DISK STATION you can also simply add the camera in the Surveillance Software on the Disk Station.</p></div></article> <!-- ###################### Lightboxes ######################## --><amp-image-lightbox id="Recording_Manual_1080p_01" layout="nodisplay"></amp-image-lightbox><amp-image-lightbox id="Recording_Manual_1080p_02" layout="nodisplay"></amp-image-lightbox><amp-image-lightbox id="Recording_Schedule_1080p_01" layout="nodisplay"></amp-image-lightbox><amp-image-lightbox id="Speicherpfad_Aufnahmen_im_IE_HD_01_EN" layout="nodisplay"></amp-image-lightbox><amp-image-lightbox id="Speicherpfad_Aufnahmen_im_IE_HD_02_EN" layout="nodisplay"></amp-image-lightbox><amp-image-lightbox id="Speicherpfad_Aufnahmen_im_IE_HD_03_EN" layout="nodisplay"></amp-image-lightbox></div></div> <% include ../_partials/content/_bluenav-general-mobile.ejs %><footer> <% include ../_partials/amp/_amp-footer.ejs %></footer></body></html>